[1] Paraguay
Date: 9 Feb 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Pan American Health Organization EID Updates, Vol. 4 No. 3 [edited]
<http://www.paho.org/english/ad/dpc/cd/eid-eer-2007-02-09.htm>

Summary of the Current Situation in Paraguay: As of 8 Feb 2007, the
epidemiological alert issued by the Ministry of Public Health and
Social Welfare of Paraguay (MSPBS) has been in effect throughout the
entire country, in view of cases of dengue and dengue hemorrhagic
(DH). To date, there have been 3 fatal cases of DH.
Up to 8 Feb 2007 (Epidemiological Week No. 6), official reports indicate:
- 3672 cases of dengue,
- 22 cases of dengue hemorrhagic,
- 3 deaths,
- Case-fatality rate: 13.6 percent,
- Departments affected: 90 percent [of the cases] in Asuncion and
Central department and 10 percent in the rest of the country,
Key Programmatic Elements:
The central focus in response to this outbreak is as follows:
- The scheduling of environmental sanitation operations complemented
by a communication strategy with emphasis on identified breeding sites.
- Environmental management complemented by chemical control in the
identified high-risk areas, commencing Wed 31 Jan 2007 and lasting
for as long as the risk of transmission and disease spread persists.
- The neighborhoods and municipalities have been classified
accordingly as very high, high, or medium priority.
In the very-high-priority municipalities, the following activities
are underway:
- Broadcasts
- Environmental management (intensified elimination of breeding sites
in all dwellings).
- Detection of cases with fever
- Spraying door to door every 3 days using motorbike backpacks
- Residual spraying every 5-7 days
- Infestation index determination sampling pre- and post-intervention.
The country currently has 200-250 brigades (special personnel plus
the armed forces), with an approximate total of 500 people,
transportation media (pickup trucks, buses, trucks, dump trucks),
fuel, maps of target areas, and forms for corresponding registries).
Results of the environmental-management operations: The various
activities that made up these operations started on 31 Jan 2007. A
total of 33 433 houses were inspected in a total of 37 targeted
neighborhoods, showing indices of infestation of between one percent
and 15 percent.
Establishment of the Situation Room: Due to current needs, local
levels report 3 times a week to the Situation Room to provide data on
patient care and community-level activities in order to maintain
up-to-date information on an ongoing basis. The Situation Room
analyzes the trends and patterns of the epidemic at the country
level. Thus, the operations of the different federal departments will
be evaluated with feedback so as to redirect strategies should the
entomological and epidemiological evidence obtained indicate the need to do so.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
